item.title: Ladders help! Easy
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

jake.bellotti:

What most servers have is a ladder which has no use. What i mean by that is when it is clicked on it will not do anything. I think in object handler you will be able to set the place where the ladder “Teleports” you to. Which will be the coordinates in which the ladder stands, but the height will be 1 instead of 0, which is ground level. Hopefully you get my very basic explanation and figure out your problem.

Ridiculousness. This offers no relevant help what so ever. He got the cannot find symbol error. Meaning he typed in something that does not exist in the java code he already has.
Say he has an empty cup. What he did was call for water that isn’t in that cup.
So he just needs to change the word “Ladders” to the correct formatting. It is case sensitive.
